title: News Minute: Here is the latest Washington news from The Associated Press
text:
News Minute: Here is the latest Washington news from The Associated Press - SWX Right Now-Sports for Spokane, CdA, Tri-Cities, WA Member Center: News Minute: Here is the latest Washington news from The Associated Press Posted: Updated: 
OLYMPIA, Wash. (AP) - A new poll shows that more than 60 percent of voters would support an initiative on next month's ballot to add state penalties to a measure to add state penalties to wildlife trafficking. The poll released today by independent pollster Stuart Elway also shows an equal number of voters support and oppose an anti-tax ballot measure. 
SEATTLE (AP) - Three suspicious fires are under investigation in Seattle, including one that damaged a mosque. Investigators say the fire early today was set in recycling and garbage containers outside a two-story building with Seattle Housing Authority offices on the first floor and the High Point Masjid Mosque on the second floor. 
SEATTLE (AP) - Boeing is celebrating the opening of an expanded Seattle Delivery Center, which it says will allow it to increase its production of its workhouse 737 airplane. The aerospace giant says the 90,000-square foot facility will help it ramp up its delivery rate of 737s from 42 a month to 52 a month in 2018. The formal opening ceremony is today, 
LYNNWOOD, Wash. (AP) - The Washington Department of Ecology is holding a public hearing in Lynnwood today on a proposal to bring more crude oil trains through the area. The Everett Herald reports it's the third session meant to help the agency and Skagit County decide what to cover in the project's environmental impact study. Department of Ecology spokesman Larry Altose says 350 people attended previous hearings in Mount Vernon and Anacortes. Copyright 2015 The Associated Press. All rights reserved.
